1️⃣ Install Java and Maven
winget install Oracle.JDK.17
winget install Apache.Maven

Verify:

java -version
mvn -version
2️⃣ Create Maven Project
mvn archetype:generate \
-DgroupId=com.example \
-DartifactId=aws-flow-demo \
-DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart \
-DinteractiveMode=false

Go inside project:

cd aws-flow-demo
3️⃣ Add AWS Dependencies

Edit pom.xml and add:

<dependency>
 <groupId>software.amazon.awssdk</groupId>
 <artifactId>aws-sdk-java</artifactId>
</dependency>

<dependency>
 <groupId>software.amazon.aws</groupId>
 <artifactId>aws-flow-sdk</artifactId>
 <version>2.x</version>
</dependency>
4️⃣ Configure AWS Credentials

Install AWS CLI:

winget install Amazon.AWSCLI

Configure:

aws configure

Enter:

Access Key
Secret Key
Region
5️⃣ Build Project
mvn clean install
6️⃣ Run Worker
mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.WorkerStarter"

Expected output:

Hello, World!